In this article, President Biden speaks at a summit and expresses his gratitude to the U.S. Fire Administration and firefighters. He reflects on his personal experiences with firefighters saving his family's lives and his admiration for their bravery. He acknowledges the risks firefighters face and the importance of their role in communities. President Biden discusses the increasing challenges of wildfires and climate change, and his administration's efforts to provide resources and support to firefighters. He mentions investments made in the American Rescue Plan and the 2023 budget, as well as initiatives to address cancer prevention, toxic exposures, and firefighter compensation. The President also highlights legislation and infrastructure investments aimed at fire prevention and response. He concludes by expressing his appreciation for firefighters and their heroic work in protecting communities.